    <div class="memory-layout">
      <!-- Left side: explanation text -->
      <div class="info">
        <h3>How memory is organized in a process</h3>
        <p>A typical process in memory is divided into logical regions:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Code / Text:</strong> program instructions (fixed size)</li>
          <li><strong>Data:</strong> global and static variables</li>
          <li><strong>Heap:</strong> grows upward; used for <code>malloc / calloc / realloc</code></li>
          <li><strong>Stack:</strong> grows downward; function calls, local variables</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          When you call <code>malloc()</code>, memory is reserved from the
          <strong>heap area</strong>. When you return from a function, its
          local variables are removed from the <strong>stack area</strong>.
        </p>

        <p>
          This diagram is a simplified visual showing which parts of memory are
          already allocated and which parts are still free.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right side: memory bar -->
      <div class="memory">
        <div class="memory-label-top">High Address</div>

        <!-- Stack section -->
        <div class="memory-block stack-section">
          <div class="block-label">Stack</div>
          <div class="memory-block-bar">
            <div class="segment" style="width: 40%"></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Free gap between stack and heap (not always, but for visual) -->
        <div class="memory-block">
          <div class="block-label">Unused</div>
          <div class="memory-block-bar">
            <div class="segment" style="width: 100%; background:#020617;"></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Heap section -->
        <div class="memory-block heap-section">
          <div class="block-label">Heap</div>
          <div class="memory-block-bar">
            <!-- allocated blocks -->
            <div class="segment allocated" style="width: 25%"></div>
            <div class="segment allocated" style="width: 15%"></div>
            <!-- free space -->
            <div class="segment free" style="width: 60%"></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Data / Code section -->
